WEBVTT

00:00:00.640 --> 00:00:02.840
<v Instructor>Welcome to the section on VPC.</v>

00:00:02.840 --> 00:00:06.380
So VPC stands for virtual private cloud and this is going

00:00:06.380 --> 00:00:08.220
to be just a small crash course.

00:00:08.220 --> 00:00:11.210
VPC is quite complicated to be honest and this is something

00:00:11.210 --> 00:00:13.760
you should know in-depth if you are going for the AWS

00:00:13.760 --> 00:00:16.580
Certified Solutions Architect Associate certification

00:00:16.580 --> 00:00:18.930
or the AWS Certified SysOps Administrator

00:00:18.930 --> 00:00:20.650
Associate certification.

00:00:20.650 --> 00:00:23.550
At the AWS Certified Cloud Practitioner level

00:00:23.550 --> 00:00:25.850
there need to know about a few about a few concepts

00:00:25.850 --> 00:00:28.130
but at a high level and what they're used for.

00:00:28.130 --> 00:00:31.190
So this includes VPC, Subnets, Internet Gateways,

00:00:31.190 --> 00:00:34.800
and NAT Gateways, Security Groups, Network ALC or NACL,

00:00:34.800 --> 00:00:38.550
and VPC Flow Logs, VPC Peering and VPC Endpoints,

00:00:38.550 --> 00:00:40.620
Site to Site VPN and Direct Connect,

00:00:40.620 --> 00:00:42.410
and finally Transit Gateway.

00:00:42.410 --> 00:00:44.870
I'm going to give you an overview of all these things.

00:00:44.870 --> 00:00:46.980
This represents less than one or two questions

00:00:46.980 --> 00:00:48.680
at your CCP exam.

00:00:48.680 --> 00:00:51.490
And then we'll have a look at the default VPC

00:00:51.490 --> 00:00:53.540
created by default by AWS for you.

00:00:53.540 --> 00:00:55.140
This is going to be our hands-on.

00:00:55.140 --> 00:00:57.670
We're not going to create our VPC from scratch.

00:00:57.670 --> 00:01:00.930
At the end of this section there is a summary lecture

00:01:00.930 --> 00:01:04.130
to explain what each of these services lined up above do

00:01:04.130 --> 00:01:05.360
and what they are.

00:01:05.360 --> 00:01:07.040
And it's okay if you don't understand it all.

00:01:07.040 --> 00:01:09.210
Hopefully that summary lecture should do it for you.

00:01:09.210 --> 00:01:12.030
And don't worry, the exam is quite high-level on VPC

00:01:12.030 --> 00:01:14.180
so if you pay attention to this lecture

00:01:14.180 --> 00:01:16.570
and this section closely, you should be good to go.

00:01:16.570 --> 00:01:17.403
Okay, that's it.

00:01:17.403 --> 00:01:18.880
I hope you're excited and I will see you

00:01:18.880 --> 00:01:20.003
in the next lecture.